      <section eId="sec_778_BBB">
        <num>778-BBB</num>
        <heading>Prohibition against unfair service agreements; recording thereof</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_778_BBB__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>No person shall record or cause to be recorded an unfair real\nestate service agreement or notice or memorandum thereof.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_778_BBB__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>If an unfair real estate service agreement is recorded in this\nstate, it shall not provide actual or constructive notice against an\notherwise bona fide purchaser or creditor.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_778_BBB__subsec_c">
          <num>(c)</num>
          <content>
            <p>If an unfair service agreement or a notice or memorandum thereof\nis recorded, any person with an interest in the real property that is\nthe subject of that agreement may apply to a court in the county where\nthe recording exists to record a court order declaring the agreement\nunenforceable.\n  * NB Effective March 12, 2026\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
